The paper deals with stochastic geometry models and optimization problems, which are typically studied in the areas of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of randomized approximation schemes also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
